and is based on Perl's extension to \s-1UTF\-8,\s0 and is probably not
displayable nor enterable by any editor.
[perl #128738] <https://rt.perl.org/Public/Bug/Display.html?id=128738>
.IP "\(bu" 4
\&\f(CW\*(C`@{x\*(C'\fR followed by a newline where \f(CW"x"\fR represents a control or non-ASCII
character no longer produces a garbled syntax error message or a crash.
[perl #128951] <https://rt.perl.org/Public/Bug/Display.html?id=128951>
.IP "\(bu" 4
An assertion failure with \f(CW\*(C`%: = 0\*(C'\fR has been fixed.
[perl #128238] <https://rt.perl.org/Public/Bug/Display.html?id=128238>
.IP "\(bu" 4
